      • newClient

        public static final CollabrifyClient newClient(Context context,
                         String gmail,
                         String displayName,
                         String accountGmail,
                         String accessToken,
                         boolean getLatest)
                                        throws InterruptedException,
                                               ExecutionException
        Creates a new client instance. Part of the initialization process requires the method to block until some internal components are ready, as such this method can throw ExecutionException and @link InterruptedException.
        Parameters:
        context - A Context object.
        gmail - The user's gmail
        displayName - The user's display name
        accountGmail - Your developer gmail
        accessToken - Your application access token
        getLatest - if set to true, set to true, the client will only retrieve the latest event. If more than one event is broadcasted before they can be retrieved, the app will only see the latest event. A use case for this is an app that broadcasts it’s entire model in each event instead of broadcasting state changes.
        Returns:
        a new CollabrifyClient instance
        Throws:
        ExecutionException
        InterruptedException

            String type,
            CollabrifyListener.CollabrifyBroadcastListener listener)

        Broadcasts a message to everyone connected to the session, must be connected when called and the session must not have ended yet
        Parameters:
        payload - Message to be sent, serialized to a byte array
        type - The type of the message
        listener - An instance of CollabrifyListener.CollabrifyBroadcastListener
        Returns:
        The submission registration id associated with the broadcasted event. This will match the submission registration id in onReceiveEvent.

        CollabrifyException

      • preventFurtherJoins

        public void preventFurtherJoins()
                         throws InterruptedException,
                                CollabrifyException,
                                ExecutionException
        Can only be called by owner of session, prevents other people from joining the session, participants who joined before this is called is unnafected. This method will block until the lock is actually applied on the backend.
        Throws:
        InterruptedException
        CollabrifyException
        ExecutionException
